From 6d34721f0af51f554166f3df9be7d8d98a8f6d4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Meta Beta Maintainer <noreply@example.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rust: crabbyavif: drop obsolete no_sanitize attributes

Rust 1.91 removed `feature(no_sanitize)` and the `no_sanitize(...)`
attribute syntax. Chromium's rust invocation here still restricts allowed
unstable features to `no_sanitize`, so switching to `sanitize` fails too.

Drop these cfg-gated attributes to keep this build path compiling.

Upstream-Status: Pending

---
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/capi/io.rs          | 1 -
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs              | 1 -
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/reformat/libyuv.rs  | 2 --
 3 files changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs b/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs
index 74f7fd730f9a..72c9694fa8f5 100644
--- a/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs
+++ b/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs
@@ -14,4 +14,3 @@
 #![deny(unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn)]
-#![cfg_attr(feature = "disable_cfi", feature(no_sanitize))]
 
 #[macro_use]
diff --git a/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/capi/io.rs b/third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/capi/io.rs
